<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,346,1791]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1690,1716]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species appears to be close to 
<taxonomicName box="[738,854,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Musca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rustica">
<emphasis box="[738,759,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[773,854,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">rustica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it by 1st flagellomere 3−4 times as long as pedicel, 2 presutural and 3 postsutural dorsocentral setae, and postpronotal lobe reddish in ground color. The male of this species is still unknown.
</paragraph>
